main event: A stationary, white luminous object that pulsated was observed for about 8 minutes in Kingsville, Canada on September 6, 1956.
interesting points: The object was reported by a civilian witness.
The object was observed from 2:15 AM to 2:23 AM.
The object disappeared on the horizon going east.
This case is listed by Project Blue Book, but the file has not been found and no other details are available.
The document also mentions two bright objects that disappeared in about 5 seconds and a third red object that was stationary for about 10 seconds.
sighted object: stationary, white luminous object that pulsated
